title: MFSL UDCD 24kt Gold Fill Pack: 702, 704, 713, 741, 746, 750, 752
description:
Filling in the rest of DigiTizeU's list of missing titles:

702 Ted Hawkins - The Next Hundred Years
704 John Hiatt - Riding With The King
713 Jimmy Buffett - Son Of A Son Of A Sailor
741 John Hiatt - Slow Turning
746 Jimmy Buffett -White Sport Coat & A Pink Crustacean
750 Counting Crows - Recovering The Satellites
752 Rob Wasserman - Trios
754 The Who - Who's Next


I still maintain the Garfunkel was never actually released. I know it's on various lists, but I've never seen a copy. Ever. Anywhere. And I own literally every gold CD Mobile Fidelity (in its original form, before the closure in 1999) ever released, including the rare samplers and various test and sound check discs. 

If anyone is interested in some of the samplers and/or test/sound check discs, let me know. I seem to remember one of the jazz samplers being a part of the initial group, but there were actually two different jazz samplers (JS-1 and JS-1A). Alan Parsons helped them create a sound check disc, which I don't think was a part of any group so far.
